# Core Development & Project Standards

## ZAG Matrix Framework Integration
All development and content must align with the ZAG Matrix framework:

### ZEN (Zeal Evolves Now)
- Mental clarity, purpose, and resilience
- Focus on helping "Alex, the Awakened Technologist" find direction
- Content should provide clarity and reduce overwhelm

### ACT (Activate Core Thrust)
- Physical well-being, relationships, and momentum
- Emphasize actionable steps and building momentum
- Focus on community and connection

### GEM (Growth Earns Mastery)
- Strategic moves, investments, and entrepreneurship
- Provide frameworks for career advancement and business growth
- Share executive experience and strategic insights

## Target Audience: "Alex, the Awakened Technologist"
- Mid-career professional who has achieved success
- Feels a pull towards greater purpose and holistic well-being
- Interested in entrepreneurial endeavors and strategic growth
- Values both professional achievement and personal fulfillment

## Technical Standards
- Use TypeScript strict mode
- Follow Next.js 14 App Router patterns
- Implement responsive design with Tailwind CSS (mobile-first)
- Write self-documenting code with clear comments
- Include JSDoc comments for complex functions
- Use semantic HTML and accessibility best practices
- Include proper error handling and loading states
- Prefer React Server Components by default; use `'use client'` only when state or browser APIs are required

## Icons (critical)
- **Never** use emojis or multi-color icons for UI
- **Only** use icons from the [Lucide](https://lucide.dev/) family
- Style: clean, minimal, monochrome; brand colors (teal, grayscale palette)
- Sizes: 16px, 20px, 24px, or 32px as context dictates

## Naming Conventions
- Components: PascalCase (e.g. `ZagMatrixSidebar.tsx`)
- Files: kebab-case (e.g. `zag-matrix-page.tsx`)
- Functions: camelCase (e.g. `handleNewsletterSignup`)
- Constants: UPPER_SNAKE_CASE (e.g. `ZAG_MATRIX_PILLARS`)

## Date stamping (PARA / project files)
- Use the **current** date when creating date-prefixed files; never guess dates
- **1P** project files: `YYYYMMDD-[description].md`
- **4A** archives: `YYYYMMDD-[description]-COMPLETED.md`
- **2A** / **3R**: no date prefix on filenames unless a specific convention requires it

## Content Principles
- Professional but approachable tone
- Connect all insights back to ZAG Matrix framework
- Use specific examples from Sheridan's executive career
- Focus on actionable, implementable advice
- Maintain authority while being accessible

## Testing Standards
- Use Playwright for end-to-end testing
- Test critical user flows; forms, navigation, blog rendering
- Validate responsive layouts and accessibility basics

## Performance & Security
- Optimize images and assets for web delivery
- Implement proper caching strategies where appropriate
- Validate user inputs on API routes; use HTTPS in production
- Monitor Core Web Vitals and performance in production
